BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260327T180000Z
DTEND:20260327T193000Z
LOCATION:GA - Room Number: 1060
SUMMARY:EASC Colloquium: Shang Wei
DESCRIPTION:Professor Wei Shang specializes in pre-modern Chinese literat
 ure and culture\, especially the fiction and drama of the Ming and Qing d
 ynasties. His research interests also include print culture\, book histor
 y and intellectual history of the same period. His book &#8220\;Rulin Wai
 shi" and Cultural Transformation in Late Imperial China (2003) addresses 
 the role of Confucian ritualism and fiction in shaping the intellectual a
 nd cultural changes of the eighteenth century. His other publications are
  concerned with Jin Ping Mei Cihua (The Plum in the Golden Vase)\, late M
 ing culture\, fiction commentary\, and medieval poetry\, including Writin
 g on Landmarks: From Yellow Crane Tower to Phoenix Pavilion (2020). He is
  the editor and co-editor of several volumes in both English and Chinese\
 , and a contributor to The Cambridge History of Chinese Literature (2010)
 .
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span data-teams="true">Professor Wei Sha
 ng specializes in pre-modern Chinese literature and culture\, especially 
 the fiction and drama of the Ming and Qing dynasties. His research intere
 sts also include print culture\, book history and intellectual history of
  the same period. His book <i>&#8220\;Rulin Waishi" and Cultural Transfor
 mation in Late Imperial China</i> (2003) addresses the role of Confucian 
 ritualism and fiction in shaping the intellectual and cultural changes of
  the eighteenth century. His other publications are concerned with <i>Jin
  Ping Mei Cihua</i> (<i>The Plum in the Golden Vase</i>)\, late Ming cult
 ure\, fiction commentary\, and medieval poetry\, including <i>Writing on 
 Landmarks: From Yellow Crane Tower to Phoenix Pavilion</i> (2020). He is 
 the editor and co-editor of several volumes in both English and Chinese\,
  and a contributor to <i>The Cambridge History of Chinese Literature</i> 
 (2010).</span></p>
